@node about " Call BBS v1.1 by Glen Martin of GREMLiNS BBS"
@prev main
@{"°°" link grems}
   _____  _              _
  /  _  \| |__  ___ _  _| |_
 |   _   | '_ \/ _ \ || |  _|
 |__| |__|_.__/\___/\_,_|\__|                        @{b}(c) GREMLiNS MAXsWARE@{ub}

 A SysOp (and/or Users) Door that allows you to enter or add a new BBS and
 it's details, which is then added to a list and displayed whenever (using
 the program CallBBS.view) by the user.

 This is a small update from Version 1.0 of CallBBS ('95 - my 1st door).

@endnode
@node run " Call BBS v1.1 by Glen Martin of GREMLiNS BBS"
@{"°°" link grems}
  _____         _        _ _
 |_   _|_ _  __| |_ __ _| | |
  |   || ' \(_-<  _/ _` | | |
 |_____|_||_/__/\__\__,_|_|_|                        @{b}(c) GREMLiNS MAXsWARE@{ub}

 Firstly (if you already haven't) create a new directory called "gremlins"
 in your doors directory. Assign "gremlins" to your doors path in the user
 startup sequence, eg: "assign gremlins: doors:gremlins" assuming you have
 the doors path assigned also.

 Move the "CallBBS" directory into the "gremlins" dir and run the door via
 a BBS menu, using  MAXs Function 34, eg: "gremlins:callbbs/callbbs", only
 if you want anybody  to axs the door to enter their BBS details.  You may
 decide not to give axs to the door,  so other SysOp's have to write you a
 msg requesting their BBS details in the listing.

 To view the BBS listing, "CallBBS.text" created by "CallBBS", you have to
 run the other door," CallBBS.view" via a BBS menu option as well.

 You get the picture? If not then @{"contact" link call} me.

@endnode
